Package edu.wpi.first.networktables

Class NetworkTableEvent

java.lang.Object
edu.wpi.first.networktables.NetworkTableEvent
public final class NetworkTableEvent
extends Object
NetworkTables event.

Events have flags. The flags are a bitmask and must be OR'ed together when listening to an event to indicate the combination of events desired to be received.

    • listener

      public final int listener
      Handle of listener that was triggered. The value returned when adding the listener can be used to map this to a specific added listener.

    • flags

      public final int flags
      Event flags. For example, kPublish if the topic was not previously published. Also indicates the data included with the event:
      • kConnected or kDisconnected: connInfo
      • kPublish, kUnpublish, or kProperties: topicInfo
      • kValueRemote, kValueLocal: valueData
      • kLogMessage: logMessage

    • connInfo

      public final ConnectionInfo connInfo
